SENATE BILL DRS15184-MG-96
Short Title: Fair Pricing & Trnspncy/340B Covered Entities. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Galey, Burgin, and Sawrey (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT ESTABLISHING FAIR PRICING AND TRANSPARENCY REQUIREMENTS FOR
3 340B COVERED ENTITIES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.(a) Chapter 131E of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
6 Article to read:
7 "Article 11C.
8 "340B Covered Entities.
9 "Part 1. Fair Pricing of 340B Drugs by Hospitals.
10 "§ 131E-214.50. Definitions.
11 The following definitions apply in this Part:
12 (1) 340B drug. – A drug that meets the definition of a "covered drug" under 42
13 U.S.C. § 256b(b)(2).
14 (2) 340B Program. – The federal 340B Drug Pricing Program authorized under
15 42 U.S.C. § 256b and 42 C.F.R. Part 10, as both are from time to time
16 amended.
17 (3) Acquisition cost. – The amount paid by a covered entity to acquire a 340B
18 drug.
19 (4) Covered entity. – Any entity described in 42 U.S.C. § 256b(a)(4)(L) or 42
20 U.S.C. § 256b(a)(4)(M).
21 "§ 131E-214.52. Fair pricing of 340B drugs by hospitals.
22 A covered entity that acquires a 340B drug for a discounted price under the 340B Program
23 shall not accept an amount greater than the acquisition cost for the 340B drug as payment for
24 dispensing, administering, or otherwise delivering the 340B drug to a patient.
25 "§ 131E-214.54. Violations constitute unfair or deceptive trade practice.
26 Any violation of this Part constitutes an unfair or deceptive trade practice in violation of
27 G.S. 75-1.1 and is subject to all of the enforcement and penalty provisions of an unfair or
28 deceptive trade practice under Article 1 of Chapter 75 of the General Statutes.
29 "Part 2. 340B Covered Entity Transparency.
30 "§ 131E-214.60. Definitions.
31 The following definitions apply in this Part:
32 (1) 340B drug. – A covered outpatient drug that has been subject to any offer for
33 reduced prices by a manufacturer pursuant to 42 U.S.C. § 256b, and is
34 purchased by a covered entity.
35 (2) 340B pricing. – Any price offered by a manufacturer to a covered entity for a
36 covered outpatient drug pursuant to 42 U.S.C. § 256b.
*DRS15184-MG-96*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) 340B Program. – The federal 340B Drug Pricing Program authorized under
2 42 U.S.C. § 256b and 42 C.F.R. Part 10, as both are from time to time
3 amended.
4 (4) Charity care. – The costs reported on Form CMS-2552-10, Worksheet S–10,
5 Line 23 or any successor form.
6 (5) Covered entity. – A covered entity, as defined in 42 U.S.C. § 256b(a)(4).
7 (6) Covered outpatient drug. – A covered outpatient drug, as defined in 42 U.S.C.
8 § 1396r-8(k)(2).
9 "§ 131E-214.62. Annual reporting requirements.
10 (a) Annually by October 1, each covered entity shall report to the Department, in the form
11 and manner required by the Department, the following information regarding the preceding
12 calendar year for the covered entity and each offsite outpatient facility, clinic, eligible offsite
13 location, or other site associated with the covered entity:
14 (1) Delineated by form of insurance or payor type, including, but not limited to,
15 Medicaid, Medicare, commercial insurance, and uninsured:
16 a. Aggregate acquisition cost paid for all 340B drugs.
17 b. Aggregate payments received by individuals, insurers, or payors for
18 all 340B drugs. For the purpose of this sub-subdivision, aggregate
19 payments include cost-sharing amounts.
20 c. The total number of prescriptions and what percentage of the covered
21 entity's prescriptions were filled with 340B drugs.
22 (2) Attestation as to whether the covered entity did any of the following:
23 a. Passed on 340B Program discounts to patients of the covered entity in
24 the form of lower cost-sharing for 340B drugs at the point of
25 dispensing or administration.
26 b. Provided a sliding fee scale for 340B drugs for patients whose family
27 income is less than two hundred percent (200%) of the federal poverty
28 level established pursuant to 42 U.S.C. § 9902.
29 (3) Total operating costs of the covered entity, including itemized costs, for each
30 of the following:
31 a. Implementation of the policies described in subdivision (2) of this
32 subsection, if applicable.
33 b. Charity care.
34 (4) Total payments made by the covered entity or any agent of the covered entity
35 to any of the following:
36 a. Any pharmacies under contract with the covered entity to dispense
37 340B drugs for 340B program-related services and other functions.
38 b. Third-party administrators, including pharmacy benefits managers, for
39 managing any components of the covered entity's participation in the
40 340B Program.
41 c. Any other third parties in connection with 340B program-related
42 compliance, legal, educational, or administrative costs.
43 (5) Total number of pharmacies under contract with the covered entity to dispense
44 340B drugs, and among those, the following information:
45 a. The number of pharmacies located out-of-state and the states in which
46 the out-of-state pharmacies are located.
47 b. Total number of prescriptions and orders for 340B drugs filled by the
48 covered entity and by each offsite outpatient facility associated with
49 the covered entity, and the percentage of such prescriptions or orders
50 that were filled at such pharmacies, delineated by in-State and
51 out-of-state pharmacies.
